                     <lbl opt="false">Cf. Bauer s.v. εὐγενής 1., 2.</lbl>
                     </xr>
               </cit>
            </etym>
            <note>
               See <bibl type="modern">Jastrow I 337a</bibl> (for 100,9 Jastrow renders <term xml:lang="jpa">גיניסיא</term>). <bibl type="modern">Levy I 452a</bibl> renders for 100,9: <term xml:lang="jpa">הוגניסיס</term> <term xml:lang="fjb">hwgnysys</term> <term xml:lang="rabbinic">hognisis</term> from Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">εὐγέναια</term>. Cf. <bibl type="modern">AC III 181a</bibl>.
            </note>
